verbose_text: Consistent with the results obtained in the primary screen, intracellular total glutathione (GSH + GSSG) levels were significantly elevated in KEAP1 KO, NAA38 KO1, and both MRP1 KO1/2 cell lines relative to the respective controls (XREF_FIG; note that NAA38 KO2 just missed the cutoff for statistical significance).
